Class SBFiducialSet

java.lang.Object
org.dcm4che2.iod.composite.Composite
org.dcm4che2.iod.composite.SpatialFiducials
org.open_ortho.dcm4ceph.core.SBFiducialSet
public class SBFiducialSet extends org.dcm4che2.iod.composite.SpatialFiducials
Reprsents a set of SB corner fiducials in DICOM format.

The fiducials can be set in distances between each other, or coordinates of each fiducial. The numbering of the fiducials is clockwise and starts from the top left corner (the fiducial with smallest x and y coordinate values). Therefore, 1 is top left, 2 is top right, 3 is bottom right and 4 is bottom left.

Author:
afm

  • Constructor Details

    • SBFiducialSet

      public SBFiducialSet(String[] uids)
      Create a new fiducial set.

      A fiducial set makes no sense if it is not related to an image, which can provide information on Pixel Spacing, necessary to put real distance to fiducial coordinates. Therefore it is necessary to create a FiducialSet with a reference to another image's SOP instance UID.

      Use loadProperties(Properties) to set configurations from properties file. Must load Properties before running init(), otherwise the fiducial coordinates will not be set.

      Parameters:
      uids - The SOP Instance UID of the referring image.

    • SBFiducialSet

      public SBFiducialSet(String[] uids, Properties fidprop)
      Create a new Fiducial Set with information passed as a Properties object.

      First loads the defaults properties, then overwrites them with the ones passed as argument.

      Parameters:
      uids - The SOP Instance UID of the referring image.
      fidprop - The fiducial set information data.

    • SBFiducialSet

      public SBFiducialSet(String[] uids, File properties)
      Create a new Fiducial Set with information passed as a File path.

      First loads the default properties, then fills in, replacing already existing properties with the ones found in the passed File.

      Parameters:
      uids - The SOP Instance UID of the referring image.
      properties - The fiducial set information data.
